# Project Structure (Generic Template)

## Directory Layout

```
{root}/
├── src/
│   ├── apps/{app-name}/              ← Deployable FE/mobile apps (NX projects)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   ├── docs/                     ← project-local: architecture/, adr/ (NO features/ — see CD-22)
│   │   └── project.json
│   ├── services/{service-name}/      ← Backend services (NX projects)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   ├── db/migrations/            ← Service-local SQL migrations (if applicable)
│   │   ├── docs/                     ← project-local: architecture/, adr/ (NO features/ — see CD-22)
│   │   ├── Dockerfile
│   │   └── project.json
│   └── shared/
│       ├── libs/{name}/              ← Shared libraries (ui, types, utils, config...)
│       └── assets/                   ← Shared static assets
├── infra/                            ← Docker, K8s, Terraform, CI configs
├── tools/generators/                 ← NX custom generators
├── docs/                             ← Workspace docs (CD-22 locked tree + org docs coexist)
│   ├── intel/                        ← CD-22: shared intel layer (catalogs, maps, snapshots) — single source of truth
│   ├── modules/M-NNN-{slug}/         ← CD-22: SDLC modules (with nested features/F-NNN-{slug}/)
│   ├── hotfixes/H-NNN-{slug}/        ← CD-22: hotfix pipelines
│   ├── inputs/                       ← CD-22: raw user-provided docs
│   ├── generated/                    ← CD-22: Office output
│   ├── architecture/                 ← Org-level: system-context, containers, tech-radar, adr/ (NOT in CD-22 lock; coexists)
│   ├── business/                     ← Org-level: vision, domain-model, stakeholders (coexists)
│   └── data/                         ← Org-level: master data, schemas (coexists)
├── docker-compose.yml
├── AGENTS.md
└── nx.json, package.json, tsconfig.base.json
```

## File Placement Patterns

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| Workspace config (nx.json, tsconfig.base.json) | Root only |
| Workspace ADR (affects ≥2 projects) | `docs/architecture/adr/` |
| Project ADR (one project only) | `{project_path}/docs/adr/` |
| Feature pipeline artifacts (CD-22) | `docs/modules/M-NNN-{slug}/features/F-NNN-{slug}/` |
| Cross-cutting feature (CD-24) | Same nested path under primary owner module; secondary modules listed in `feature-catalog.features[].consumed_by_modules[]` |
| Hotfix pipeline (CD-22) | `docs/hotfixes/H-NNN-{slug}/` |
| Module pipeline (CD-22) | `docs/modules/M-NNN-{slug}/` |
| Intel layer (CD-10/CD-22) | `docs/intel/` (catalogs, maps, registries) |
| Shared components (≥2 apps) | `src/shared/libs/ui/src/` |
| Service Dockerfile | Collocated: `{project_path}/Dockerfile` |

## Docs Path Formula (CD-22 locked tree)

```
project-path = src/apps/{name}  OR  src/services/{name}    # code location
docs-path    = docs/modules/M-NNN-{slug}/features/F-NNN-{slug}    # SDLC docs (CD-22)
adr-path     = {project-path}/docs/adr/                    # project-local ADRs
intel-path   = docs/intel/                                 # shared intel (CD-10)
```

Feature locate: **`Bash("ai-kit sdlc resolve --workspace . --kind feature --id F-NNN")`** (atomic, ai-kit Node-native). ai-kit CLI unavailable → BLOCK per ADR-005 D3 (no Glob fallback). Map source: `docs/intel/feature-map.yaml` (per ADR-003 D9-4).

## NX Project Tags Convention

Every `project.json` should include:
```json
{
  "tags": [
    "scope:{project-name}",
    "type:{app|service|lib}",
    "platform:{web|mobile|node|dotnet|python|java|rust|...}",
    "ui-template:{template-name|none}"
  ]
}
```

Agents use NX MCP `get_project_details({name})` to read tags — no manual lookup needed.
